  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rebuild Earthquake Resilient Schools in Nepal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2015, two violent earthquakes struck Nepal affecting 5.4 million people. AHAH arrived 72 hours after the first, to see how we could help. After six+ months of rubble removal and constructing camps, clinics and homes, we began to focus on rebuilding resilient schools. This program, now entering its fifth year, is our holistic approach to helping as many overlooked rural communities as possible recover -- and recover stronger -- by rebuilding the schools at the center of community life.</narrative>
  </description>
